'''Henryk Jaskuła''' (born 22 October 1923 in [[Radziszów]]) is a [[yachtsman]], sailing [[Captain (nautical)|captain]], and [[electrician]]. He was the first [[Poland|Pole]] to perform a [[single-handed sailing|single-handed]] non-stop [[circumnavigation]] of the [[globe]]. He achieved it on the yacht ''Dar Przemyśla''.

Jaskuła became the third man to circumnavigate the globe non-stop and single-handed on 20 May 1980, the day he returned to [[Gdynia]].

